"content": "<style>\nh1.thlex-title { font-size: 1.3em; margin: 0 0 0.4em; }\n.thlex-key { color: #888; font-size: 0.85em; font-weight: normal; margin-right: 0.4em; }\nnav.thlex-index { margin: 0.5em 0 0.75em; }\nnav.thlex-index ul { margin: 0; padding-left: 1.2em; }\nnav.thlex-index li { margin: 0.15em 0; font-size: 0.95em; }\n.thlex-section { margin: 0.6em 0; }\nh2.thlex-heading { font-size: 1em; margin: 0.5em 0 0.2em; }\nh3.thlex-subheading { font-size: 0.95em; font-weight: normal; font-style: italic; margin: 0.2em 0; }\n.thlex-language-sets { margin: 0.3em 0 0.3em 1em; }\n.thlex-language-set { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 0.75em; border-left: 3px solid #e0e0e0; }\n.thlex-language { font-size: 0.8em; color: #888; margin-right: 0.4em; }\n.thlex-lemma { font-weight: bold; font-family: serif; }\n.thlex-translit { color: #555; font-style: italic; font-size: 0.9em; margin-left: 0.3em; }\n.thlex-refs { font-size: 0.85em; color: #444; margin-top: 0.15em; }\n.thlex-paragraphs p { margin: 0.35em 0; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.5; }\n.thlex-image { margin: 0.5em 0; display: block; }\n.thlex-image img { max-width: 100%; height: auto; display: block; }\nfigcaption.thlex-caption { font-size: 0.85em; color: #555; font-style: italic; margin-top: 0.2em; }\n.thlex-abbr { border-bottom: 1px dotted #888; cursor: help; }\n.thlex-xref { color: #1a5fb4; }\nspan[data-bnType=\"bibleReference\"] { color: #1a5fb4; }\ntable.thlex-table { border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 0.9em; margin: 0.5em 0; }\ntable.thlex-table td { padding: 0.2em 0.6em; vertical-align: top; border: 1px solid #ddd; }\ntable.thlex-table tr:first-child td { font-weight: bold; background: #f5f5f5; }\nul.thlex-index-list { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.6; }\nul.thlex-index-list ul { margin: 0.1em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; }\n.thlex-index-key { font-weight: bold; font-style: italic; }\n</style><h1 class=\"thlex-title\" id=\"REALIA:1.7.6\"><span class=\"thlex-key\">1.7.6</span> Writing tablet, tablet of brass/bronze</h1><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">References:</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-sets\">\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">גִּלָּיוֹן</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(gilayon)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa8:1\">ISA 8:1</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">לוּחַ</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(luach)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod24:12\">EXO 24:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod31:18\">EXO 31:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod31:18\">EXO 31:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod32:15\">EXO 32:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod32:15\">EXO 32:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod32:16\">EXO 32:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod32:16\">EXO 32:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod32:19\">EXO 32:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod34:1\">EXO 34:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod34:1\">EXO 34:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod34:1\">EXO 34:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod34:4\">EXO 34:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod34:4\">EXO 34:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod34:28\">EXO 34:28</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod34:29\">EXO 34:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut4:13\">DEU 4:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut5:22\">DEU 5:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut9:9\">DEU 9:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut9:9\">DEU 9:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut9:10\">DEU 9:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut9:11\">DEU 9:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut9:11\">DEU 9:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut9:15\">DEU 9:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut9:17\">DEU 9:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut10:1\">DEU 10:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut10:2\">DEU 10:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut10:2\">DEU 10:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut10:3\">DEU 10:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut10:3\">DEU 10:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut10:4\">DEU 10:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut10:5\">DEU 10:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs8:9\">1KI 8:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr5:10\">2CH 5:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov3:3\">PRO 3:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov7:3\">PRO 7:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa30:8\">ISA 30:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer17:1\">JER 17:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hab2:2\">HAB 2:2</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Greek</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">δέλτος</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(deltos)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Macc8:22\">1MA 8:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Macc14:18\">1MA 14:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Macc14:26\">1MA 14:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Macc14:48\">1MA 14:48</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Greek</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">πινακίδιον</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(pinakidion)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:63\">LUK 1:63</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Latin</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">buxus</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Esd14:24\">2ES 14:24</a></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">Description:</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>\n            <figure class=\"thlex-image\"><img class=\"thlex-img\" src=\"images/WEB-0355_tablet.jpg\" alt=\"Wax writing tablet\"><figcaption class=\"thlex-caption\">Wax writing tablet (Metropolitan Museum of Art, CC0, MMA)</figcaption></figure>The writing tablet was a small, flat board, normally made of wood. It was coated on one side with a thin layer of wax. A pointed stick or stylus was used to make marks and letters in the wax layer for short messages. After use, the wax could be smoothed out and used again. Several tablets could be connected along one edge by cord in order to make a kind of book. See the illustration at <a class=\"thlex-xref\" data-bnType=\"lexiconLink\" data-collection=\"\" data-key=\"\" href=\"#\">1.7.5 Stylus&lt;REALIA:1.7.5&gt;</a>. It is possible that the Old Testament references are to tablets made of clay, metal or stone, on which words were scratched directly with a hard, pointed object.</p>\n<p>The tablets mentioned in 1 Maccabees were flat pieces of polished brass or bronze on which words were inscribed. The sizes of these tablets are unknown, but they would probably not have been very large.</p>\n<hr/>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">Translation:</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>Translators should avoid a word that indicates a modern “tablet” of writing paper.</p>\n<p>\n            <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov3:3\">PRO 3:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov7:3\">PRO 7:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer17:1\">JER 17:1</a>: The Hebrew word <em>luach</em> has a figurative meaning in these passages and may be rendered without reference to an actual writing tablet; for example, <abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Good News Translation (1992)\">GNT</abbr> renders <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov7:3\">PRO 7:3</a> b as “write it on your heart,” and <abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Italian Common Language Version\">ITCL</abbr> has “guard them in your heart like a treasure.”</p>\n<p>Although one or two of the references with the Greek word <em>deltos</em> speak of the tablets as containing “letters” (that is, correspondence), such tablets were not the normal medium for letters. According to <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Macc8:22\">1MA 8:22</a>, they were special memorial documents, intended “as a memorial of peace and alliance” (<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Revised Standard Version (1952)\">RSV</abbr>). Some cultures may have special documents that are exchanged between people groups when they make treaties or alliances.</p>\n</div>\n</div>",
